# Raw sources

`~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/` contains original crawled documents. **Do not modify manually.**

Changes must go through approved crawlers in `scripts/`:

- `crawl_citizens_advice.py` → `~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/citizens-advice/`
- `crawl_advicenow.py` → `~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/advicenow/`
- `crawl_cpr.py` → `~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/cpr/`
- `crawl_lawhive.py` → `~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/lawhive/`
- `crawl_taylor_rose.py` → `~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/taylor-rose/` (Taylor Rose [Insights](https://www.taylor-rose.co.uk/insights))
- `crawl_legislation_govuk.py` → `~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/legislation-govuk/` ([legislation.gov.uk](https://www.legislation.gov.uk/))
- `crawl_sentencing_council.py` → `~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/sentencing-council/` ([Sentencing Council](https://sentencingcouncil.org.uk/guidelines/magistrates/))
- `crawl_govuk.py` → `~/Projects/legal_shaman/raw/govuk/` ([GOV.UK](https://www.gov.uk/))

When reading raw files for wiki ingestion, use the YAML frontmatter (`source`, `url`, `title`, `crawl_date`) for attribution. Preserve source meaning when summarising into wiki pages.
